<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ861215-0190 </DOCNO><HL> Blocker Energy Sells 65% Stake</HL><DD> 12/15/86</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> BLKTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> HOUSTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Blocker Energy Corp. said it completed the previously reported sale of a 65% stake in the company to BEC Ventures of Fort Worth, Texas.    BEC Ventures is a partnership controlled by Richard Rainwater, formerly an investment adviser with Bass Brothers Enterprises. Members of Blocker management hold a 10% share of BEC Ventures, which also acquired 400,000 shares of a new series of Blocker preferred stock and assumed $12 million of debt.    Blocker's creditors agreed to exchange $82.4 million in debt outstanding for 10% of Blocker's common stock outstanding and 44,445 shares of a new series of preferred stock.    Blocker, which operates drilling rigs, said the transaction reduced its debt outstanding to about $17.5 million from $99.9 million while boosting stockholders' equity to $40.4 million. </TEXT></DOC>